    "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAdd an event before search starts with `/`, `*`, `?` and after it stops.\r\n\r\nThis can be useful for plugins that would set/unset options and enable/disable keymaps before and after the search.\r\n\r\nA basic usage would be to toggle the scrolloff`autocmd SearchStart set scrolloff=999`, `autocmd SearchStop set scrolloff=0` so when we are searching the text is always in the middle (sometimes it is put on the bottom and is hard to see the next lines)\r\n\r\nA more advanced usage would be a plugin that enables keymappings available only during search such as `i` to toggle insensitive search, `p` to toggle a side panel with all avaiable search results, using `w` to toggle search on all visible `windows`, `t` to toggle search on all tabs, `r` to toggle regex search.\r\n\r\nI am not aware if such plugin exists, but I am just giving an example of what could be accomplished: customization and more powerful search behavior.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nTwo new events `SearchStart` and `SearchStop` just like `BufEnter`, `WinNew`, etc ...",
