            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Describe an exact scenario showing exact steps.\r\n\r\nExample 1: Plugin / userscript that toggles the `scrolloff` like `autocmd SearchStart set scrolloff=99 sidescrolloff=99` and `autocmd SearchStop set scrolloff=0 sidescrolloff` so when we are searching the text is always in the middle, otherwise sometimes the next search is on the very bottom and end of screen and it is hard to see the next lines (but some people prefer `scrolloff=0 sidescrolloff=1` in normal mode, so that shall be rested)\r\n\r\nExample 2: It could be used to create a plugin that enables keymappings available only during search such as i to toggle insensitive search, p to toggle a side panel with all avaiable search results, using w to toggle search on all visible windows, t to toggle search on all tabs, r to toggle regex search. After the search stops, these mappings are reverted.\r\n\r\n> Is this for incremental search while typing in the / prompt? That can already be achieved via CmdlineEnter/CmdlineLeave.\r\n\r\nNot, it is not for incremental search.\r\n\r\n",
